From the balance sheet, I can see:
- Total Current Assets at the end of the period: $10,619,895.35
- Total Current Liabilities at the end of the period: $624,988.48

Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
Current Ratio = $10,619,895.35 / $624,988.48
